# Functions in C++

A function lets you give a name to reusable logic.

<!-- vixnote:cell id="function-cpp" kind="cpp" title="Function example" -->
```cpp
#include <iostream>

int add(int a, int b)
{
  return a + b;
}

int main()
{
  int result = add(3, 4);

  std::cout << "3 + 4 = " << result << std::endl;

  return 0;
}
```

<!-- vixnote:cell id="takeaway" kind="markdown" -->
Functions help make code easier to read, test, and reuse.
